V.A.G. Kredit Bank GmbH,the credit bank subsidiary of Volkswagen AG &lt;VOWG.F>, said itwas optimistic for 1987 after raising turnover and balancesheet total in 1986.    V.A.G., Which finances the purchase of new and used carsfor VW customers, said 1986 profits met expectations but gaveno details.    Financing turnover rose by 4.2 billion marks to 24.4billion in 1986. Balance sheet total increased by 228 mln marksto 2.84 billion. REUTER&#3;